Calculator by Me
This project is a simple calculator built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It allows users to perform basic arithmetic operations.

Features
Basic Arithmetic Operations: Addition (+), Subtraction (-), Multiplication (*), and Division (/).
Additional Functions: Clear All (AC), Delete Last Digit (DEL), Percentage Calculation (%).
Responsive Design: The calculator is designed to be responsive and works on various screen sizes.
Technologies Used
HTML: Structure of the calculator interface.
CSS: Styling for layout and visual appearance.
JavaScript: Functionality for handling user input and performing calculations.
Files Included
index.html: Contains the HTML structure for the calculator.
style10.css: External stylesheet for defining layout and design.
script10.js: JavaScript file for implementing calculator functionalities.
Usage
Launching the Calculator: Open index.html in a web browser.
Performing Calculations: Click on the numeric buttons (0-9), operators (+, -, *, /), and function buttons (AC, DEL, %, .) to perform calculations.
Clearing and Deleting: Use AC to clear the input box, DEL to delete the last digit, and % for percentage calculations.
Getting Results: Press = to display the result of the calculation in the input box.
Customization
Adding Functionality: Modify script10.js to add more operations or advanced features.
Styling: Customize the appearance of the calculator by editing style10.css.
Enhancements: Expand the calculator with scientific functions, memory features, or history tracking.
Compatibility
The calculator is compatible with modern web browsers that support HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript.
Notes
Ensure all JavaScript functionalities (script10.js) are correctly linked and functioning as expected.
Verify paths to external resources (style10.css and script10.js) for proper integration.
Customize styles and layout in style10.css to suit your design preferences.
